<h2 class="login__heading">Login</h2>
<div class="login__wrapper">
  <section class="login__form-card">
    <form class="login__form" action="/login" method="POST">
      <div class="login__input-wrapper">
        <label class="login__label" for="email">Email</label>
        <input
          class="login__input"
          type="email"
          name="email"
          value="<%= locals.oldInput?.email || '' %>"
          placeholder="your email..."
          required
        />
      </div>
      <div class="login__input-wrapper">
        <label class="login__label for="password">Password</label>
        <input
          class="login__input"
          type="password"
          name="password"
          placeholder="your password..."
          required
        />
      </div>
      <div class="login__submit-btn-wrapper">
        <button class="login__submit-btn btn-filled" type="submit">Login</button>
        <% if (locals.errors) { %>
        <div class="login__error-message">
          <% if (locals.errors.length > 0) { %>
            <ul>
              <% locals.errors.forEach(error => { %>
                <li><%= error.msg %></li>
              <% }) %>
            </ul>
          <% } %>
        </>
      </div>
      <% } %>
      <p class="login__toggle-login">
        Don't have an account?
        <a class="login__login-link" href="/register">Register</a>
      </p>
    </form>
    <hr class="login__form-card-hr">
    <div class="login__requirements-wrapper">
      <p class="login__requirements-info">
        NB! Both fields required for successful login
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="login__info-card">
    <h2 class="login__info-main-heading">Information</h2>
    <h3 class="login__info-heading">How to login</h3>
    <p class="login__info-text">
      In order to login you must provide your email and password.
    </p>
    <h3 class="login__info-heading">What to expect</h3>
    <p class="login__info-text">
      When you are successfully logged in you will be directed to your home page where you can see information about your user and become a house member - if you have the secret password... You are also able to go to the messages area to view messages!
    </p>
    <h3 class="login__info-heading">Becoming a house member</h3>
    <p class="login__info-text">
      Becoming a house member requires you to insert a secret password into the ‘Become a member’ field on your ‘home’ page. The idea is that you stick around and get noticed until a house member deem you worthy as a member and gives you the secret password...
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
